Projects

MyFitnessMeter

MyFitnessMeter is a web app that allows users to set fitness goals, track workouts, and keep a diary of food intake. Technologies used include but not limited to: JavaScript, React, Python, Flask, SQL, MyPlot, HTML, CSS

SoundCloud Clone

SoundCloud Clone is my first attempt at making a working web app that allows users to upload and play songs. Technologies used include but not limited to: JavaScript, React, Node.js, Sequelize, HTML, CSS

Yell

Yell is a web app that allows users to search for and leave reviews for restaurants. Technologies used include but not limited to: Python, Flask, JavaScript, React, SQLAlchemy, HTML, CSS

ABOUT

Hi, I'm Anthony. Born in Louisiana and raised in California, I’ve got a mix of laid-back Southern charm and a free-spirited West Coast vibe. I’m a software engineer with a background in quality control in biotech. I also drive for Uber sometimes—it’s a fun way to meet new people, explore new places, and enjoy the drive. I’m naturally curious and love learning new things.

I currently use React, Redux, JavaScript, HTML5, and CSS for the frontend, and Python, Flask, SQLAlchemy, Node.js, Express.js, Sequelize, SQL, and PostgreSQL for the backend. I also have experience with AWS, Docker, and Git. I am dedicated to continuous learning and quickly adapt to new technologies. With my expertise and dedication, I am confident I can make a significant impact on your team.
